## function __canvas__\(auto\_prepare=True, \*\*style\_args\)

Creates a new `canvas` object. For a list of arguments and keywords,
see:

- [/python/canvas/](/python/canvas/)

__Example:__

{% highlight python %}
my_canvas = canvas()
{% endhighlight %}

__Keywords:__

- `auto_prepare` -- No description
	- Default: True

__Keyword dict:__

- `**style_args`: No description.

__Returns:__

A `canvas` object.

- Type: canvas

</div>

